  "title": "JavaScript / jQuery DOM Selectors",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "JavaScript / jQuery DOM Selectors"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "jQuery vs JavaScript"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "jQuery was created in 2006 by John Resig. \nIt was designed to handle Browser Incompatibilities and to simplify HTML DOM Manipulation, Event Handling, Animations, and Ajax."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "However, after JavaScript Version 5 (2009), most of the jQuery utilities can be solved with a few lines of standard JavaScript:"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Finding HTML Element by Id"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Return the element with id=\"id01\":"
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
          "code": "myElement = $(\"#id01\");"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
          "code": "myElement = document.getElementById(\"id01\");"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Finding HTML Elements by Tag Name"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Return all <p> elements:"
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
          "code": "myElements = $(\"p\");"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
          "code": "myElements = document.getElementsByTagName(\"p\");"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Finding HTML Elements by Class Name"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Return all elements with class=\"intro\"."
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
          "code": "myElements = $(\".intro\");"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
          "code": "myElements = document.getElementsByClassName(\"intro\");"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Finding HTML Elements by CSS Selectors"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Return a list of all <p> elements with class=\"intro\"."
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
          "code": "myElements = $(\"p.intro\");"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
          "code": "myElements = document.querySelectorAll(\"p.intro\");"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}